cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper proposes a framework for self-supervised learning of long horizon tasks through visual subgoal generation and planning. The tasks involve manipulation in cluttered scenes, which suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of planning algorithms and reinforcement learning also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the application of the method to real-world scenes suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
